  "text": "Cellular uptake and degradation of 125 I-mLDL. Cell lines were grown in 15-mm wells to ‫ف‬ 90% confluence in serum-supplemented media. For the experimental incubations, cells were changed to a serum-free 1:1 mixture of Waymouth's MD-705/1 and MEM supplemented with 0.2% fatty acid-free BSA, 125 I-mLDL (5 g/ml), and either LpL (5 g/ml) or a matching volume of lipase buffer [CITATION_1] . Cells were incubated for up to 5 h in these media at 37 Њ C, then cell association and cell-specific degradation of 125 I-lipoproteins were assayed as described previously [CITATION_2] 77) . In some experiments, cell association was separated into cell-surface and intracellular fractions by incubating the cells for 30 min at 4 Њ C in the presence of 10 mg heparin per milliliter, which releases surface-bound material (77).",
